      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Overview of the elastic query feature",
      "pos": [
        159,
        196
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure SQL Database Elastic Database query (preview) overview",
      "pos": [
        554,
        614
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Elastic Database query feature<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, in preview, enables you to run a Transact-SQL query that spans multiple databases in Azure SQL Database.",
      "pos": [
        616,
        760
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It allows you to connect Microsoft and third party tools (Excel, PowerBI, Tableau, etc.) to data tiers with multiple databases, especially when those databases share a common schema (also known as horizontal partitioning or sharding).",
      "pos": [
        761,
        995
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Using this feature, you can scale out queries to large data tiers in SQL Database and visualize the results in business intelligence (BI) reports.",
      "pos": [
        996,
        1142
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1144,
        1299
      ],
      "content": "To begin building an elastic database query application, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Getting started with  Elastic Database query<ept id=\"p1\">](sql-database-elastic-query-getting-started.md)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Elastic database query scenarios",
      "pos": [
        1304,
        1336
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The goal of the Elastic Database query is to facilitate reporting scenarios where multiple databases contribute rows into a single overall result.",
      "pos": [
        1338,
        1484
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The query can either be composed by the user or application directly, or indirectly through tools that are connected to the query database.",
      "pos": [
        1485,
        1624
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is especially useful when creating reports, using commercial BI or data integration tools—or any software that cannot be changed.",
      "pos": [
        1625,
        1759
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With an elastic database query, you can easily query across several databases using the familiar SQL Server connectivity experience in tools such as Excel, PowerBI, Tableau, or Cognos.",
      "pos": [
        1760,
        1944
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An elastic database query also allows easy access to an entire collection of databases through queries issued by SQL Server Management Studio or Visual Studio, and facilitates cross-database querying from Entity Framework or other ORM environments.",
      "pos": [
        1946,
        2194
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Figure 1 shows a scenario where an existing cloud application (which uses the Elastic Database tools library) builds on a scaled-out data tier, and an elastic database query is used for cross-database reporting.",
      "pos": [
        2195,
        2406
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Figure 1",
      "pos": [
        2410,
        2418
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "![Elastic database query used on scaled-out data tier][1]",
      "pos": [
        2422,
        2479
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The data tier is scaled out across many databases using a common schema.",
      "pos": [
        2481,
        2553
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This approach is also known as horizontal partitioning or sharding.",
      "pos": [
        2554,
        2621
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The partitioning can be performed and managed using (1) the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Elastic Database client library<ept id=\"p1\">](http://www.nuget.org/packages/Microsoft.Azure.SqlDatabase.ElasticScale.Client/)</ept> or (2) using an application-specific model for distributing data across multiple databases.",
      "pos": [
        2622,
        2887
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With this topology, reports often have to span multiple databases.",
      "pos": [
        2888,
        2954
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With an elastic database query, you can now connect to a single SQL database, and query results from the remote databases appear as if generated from a single virtual database.",
      "pos": [
        2955,
        3131
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> Elastic database query works best for occasional reporting scenarios where most of the processing can be performed on the data tier.",
      "pos": [
        3135,
        3280
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For heavy reporting workloads or data warehousing scenarios with more complex queries, also consider using <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure SQL Data Warehouse<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/services/sql-data-warehouse/)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3281,
        3472
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Elastic Database query topology",
      "pos": [
        3478,
        3509
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Using an elastic database query to perform reporting tasks over a horizontally partitioned data tier requires an elastic scale shard map to represent the databases of the data tier.",
      "pos": [
        3511,
        3692
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Typically, only a single shard map is used in this scenario and a dedicated database with elastic database query capabilities serves as the entry point for reporting queries.",
      "pos": [
        3693,
        3867
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Only this dedicated database needs to be configured with elastic database query objects, as described below.",
      "pos": [
        3868,
        3976
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Figure 2 illustrates this topology and its configuration with the elastic database query database and shard map.",
      "pos": [
        3977,
        4089
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> The dedicated elastic database query database must be a SQL DB v12 database and initially only the Premium tier is supported.",
      "pos": [
        4093,
        4231
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are no restrictions on the shards themselves.",
      "pos": [
        4232,
        4283
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Figure 2",
      "pos": [
        4287,
        4295
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "![Use Elastic Database query for Reporting over Sharded Tiers][2]",
      "pos": [
        4299,
        4364
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "(A <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>shardlet<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is all of the data associated with a single value of a sharding key on a shard.",
      "pos": [
        4366,
        4461
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>sharding key<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is a column value that determines how data is distributed across shards.",
      "pos": [
        4462,
        4553
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, data distributed by regions may have region IDs as the sharding key.",
      "pos": [
        4554,
        4635
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more details, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>elastic scale glossary<ept id=\"p1\">](sql-database-elastic-scale-glossary.md)</ept>.)",
      "pos": [
        4636,
        4728
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Over time, additional topologies will be supported by the Elastic Database query feature.",
      "pos": [
        4731,
        4820
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This article will be updated to reflect new features as they become available.",
      "pos": [
        4821,
        4899
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enabling elastic queries by configuring a shard map",
      "pos": [
        4904,
        4955
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Creating an elastic database query solution requires the Elastic Database tools <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>shard map<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](sql-database-elastic-scale-shard-map-management.md)</ept> to represent the remote databases to an elastic database query.",
      "pos": [
        4957,
        5168
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you are already using the Elastic Database client library, you can use your existing shard map.",
      "pos": [
        5169,
        5267
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Otherwise, you need to create a shard map using Elastic Database tools.",
      "pos": [
        5268,
        5339
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following example C# code shows how to create a shard map with a single remote database added as a shard.",
      "pos": [
        5341,
        5450
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5941,
        6063
      ],
      "content": "For more details on shard maps, please refer to <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Shardmap management<ept id=\"p1\">](sql-database-elastic-scale-shard-map-management.md)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "To use the Elastic Database query feature, you must first create the shard map and register your remote databases as shards.",
      "pos": [
        6065,
        6189
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is a one-time operation.",
      "pos": [
        6190,
        6219
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You only need to change your shard map when you add or remove remote databases—which are incremental operations on an existing shard map.",
      "pos": [
        6220,
        6357
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Creating elastic database query database objects",
      "pos": [
        6363,
        6411
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To describe the remote tables that can be accessed from an elastic database query endpoint, we introduce the ability to define external tables that will appear to your application and to 3rd party tools as if they were local tables.",
      "pos": [
        6413,
        6645
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Queries can be submitted against these database objects implicitly through the tools, or explicitly from SQL Server Management Studio, Visual Studio Data Tools, or from an application.",
      "pos": [
        6646,
        6830
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The elastic database query executes like any other Transact-SQL statement—with the notable difference that query will distribute the processing against the potentially many remote databases underlying the external objects.",
      "pos": [
        6831,
        7053
      ]
    },
    {
