    },
    {
      "content": "External tables",
      "pos": [
        9828,
        9843
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With the Elastic Database query, we extend the existing external table syntax to refer to tables that are partitioned across (several) remote database(s) in Azure SQL DB.",
      "pos": [
        9845,
        10015
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Using the external data source concept from above, the syntax to create and drop external tables is defined as follows:",
      "pos": [
        10016,
        10135
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The sharding policy controls whether a table is treated as a sharded table or as a replicated table.",
      "pos": [
        10494,
        10594
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With a sharded table, the data from different shards does not overlap.",
      "pos": [
        10595,
        10665
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Replicated tables in turn have the same data on every shard.",
      "pos": [
        10666,
        10726
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The query processor relies on this information for correct and more efficient query processing.",
      "pos": [
        10727,
        10822
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The round robin distribution indicates that an application specific method for distributing the data of that table is used.",
      "pos": [
        10823,
        10946
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        11024,
        11186
      ],
